e visible","Hard palate and base of the uvula are visible","Soft palate and the uvula are visible","Soft palate, uvula, and pillars are visible","Only the hard palate is visible"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn Class II of the modified Mallampati classification, the\u003Cstrong\u003E soft palate and the uvula are visible\u003C/strong\u003E. This classification helps in assessing the potential difficulty of intubation by examining the visibility of oral structures when the patient opens their mouth and protrudes their tongue. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe full Mallampati scoring system is as follows:\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EClass I: the \u003Cstrong\u003Esoft palate, uvula, and pillars\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Eare visible\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EClass II: the\u003Cstrong\u003E soft palate and the uvula are visible\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EClass III: the \u003Cstrong\u003Esoft palate and base of the uvula are visible\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EClass IV: \u003Cstrong\u003Eonly the hard palate is visible\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe option \u003Cstrong\u003Ehard palate and base of the uvula\u003C/strong\u003E visible is not a standard description in this classification.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The modified Mallampati classification is used to predict the difficulty of intubation based on the visibility of oral structures.","In Class II of the modified Mallampati classification, the soft palate and the uvula are visible."],"references":["Stutz EW, Rondeau B. Mallampati Score. 2023 Aug 5. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 36256766.","Paxton E, Parotto M. The best visible Mallampati score-too good to be true? Can J Anaesth. 2024 Oct;71(10):1339-1343. English. doi: 10.1007/s12630-024-02814-1. Epub 2024 Aug 15. PMID: 39147991.","Chatterjee A, Maheshwari VS, Mahanty PR, Nag DS, Shukla R. A Prospective, Comparative Study to Evaluate the Diagnostic Accuracy of Mallampati Grading in Supine and Sitting Positions for Prediction of Difficult Airway. Cureus. 2021 Oct 3;13(10):e18465. doi: 10.7759/cureus.18465. PMID: 34754631; PMCID: PMC8569641.","Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49739"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15470"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49739","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49739"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-23T12:08:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-23T12:09:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8161"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64307"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null